# Interview Story (STAR Format)

## Project

Technology Cost Allocation Automation

---

## Situation

The organization managed multiple technology services including cybersecurity licenses, backup solutions, email security, monitoring tools, and leased technology assets.

The monthly invoice validation process was highly manual and required analysts to review inventory files, identify assigned users, map cost centers, calculate allocations, and generate prefactura reports for financial validation.

The process typically required approximately 60 minutes per invoice and was vulnerable to calculation errors, inconsistencies, delays, and incorrect cost allocations.

---

## Task

My responsibility was to improve the efficiency, accuracy, and consistency of the cost allocation process while maintaining the ability to validate supplier invoices and support financial reporting requirements.

The objective was to reduce manual effort, improve traceability, and standardize the allocation methodology.

---

## Action

I analyzed the existing workflow and identified the most repetitive and error-prone activities.

I designed and developed a VBA-based automation solution using Microsoft Excel.

The solution included:

* Automated inventory imports.
* User-to-cost-center mapping.
* Allocation logic based on predefined business rules.
* Consolidation of multiple technology services into a centralized reporting layer.
* Automated prefactura generation.
* Cost center summary reporting.
* Data normalization controls to improve matching accuracy.

I also structured the solution so different technology services could be processed independently while maintaining a consolidated reporting model.

---

## Result

The automation reduced invoice validation effort from approximately 60 minutes to 10 minutes, representing an efficiency improvement of more than 80%.

Additional benefits included:

* Improved allocation accuracy.
* Reduced manual calculations.
* Increased reporting consistency.
* Better visibility of technology expenses by cost center.
* Improved traceability for financial validation activities.
* Reduced operational risk associated with manual processing.

The solution became the standard mechanism used to support technology cost allocation and invoice validation activities.

---

